  "text": "Another limitation of our experimental model was the possible influence of anesthesia on the pulmonary reflexes. It was previously shown that intravenous anesthesia with barbiturates can inhibit the reflex bronchoconstriction induced by histamine aerosol [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, a very small amount of HCl administered into the trachea resulted in a substantial bronchoconstriction in our experimental model, and, in GP with chronic airway inflammation, even intratracheal administration of only 20 l of saline resulted in bronchoconstriction. Using anesthesia with xylazine, we obtained the same results: infusion of acid into the lower esophagus did not result in significant pulmonary effects.",
